curacy                           0.59    872862\n","   macro avg       0.56      0.61      0.53    872862\n","weighted avg       0.76      0.59      0.64    872862\n","\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 600x400 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Tradeoffs TEXT:\n"],"metadata":{"id":"s0V1P-t5oOUS"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"0FATCFLXV10y"},"source":["## ✅ Summary\n","\n","In this project, we built and evaluated a machine learning model to predict flight delays using U.S. domestic flight data. We performed end-to-end steps including:\n","\n","- Data cleaning and time-based feature engineering\n","- Encoding high-cardinality features like airport codes\n","- Training a LightGBM model for fast and accurate classification\n","- Hyperparameter tuning with GridSearchCV\n","- Final evaluation using accuracy, classification report, and confusion matrix\n","\n","The final model achieved strong predictive performance, with clear interpretability. This project demonstrates a real-world machine learning pipeline and can be taken up for further fine tuning to make it deployable for use in operations and or travel forecasting tools.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["---\n","\n","# Final Model Comparison – Test Set Results\n","\n","Both models were evaluated on the same unseen test dataset (872,862 flights). The confusion matrices help us clearly understand how each model behaves.\n","\n","---\n","\n","## Logistic Regression (Balanced)\n","\n","Confusion Matrix (Test):\n","\n","* True Negatives (correct on-time): **418,928**\n","* False Positives (false delay alarms): **294,418**\n","* False Negatives (missed delays): **59,300**\n","* True Positives (correct delays): **100,216**\n","\n","### What this means:\n","\n","* The model correctly caught **100,216 delayed flights**.\n","* However, it incorrectly flagged **294,418 on-time flights as delayed**.\n","* That means it produces **many false alarms**.\n","* Overall accuracy was only **59%**.\n","* Recall for delayed flights was high (63%), but precision was low (25%).\n","\n","In simple terms:\n","\n","> Logistic Regression aggressively predicts delays. It catches many real delays but creates too many false warnings, making it less practical.\n","\n","---\n","\n","##  LightGBM (Tuned Threshold)\n","\n","Confusion Matrix (Test):\n","\n","* True Negatives (correct on-time): **708,186**\n","* False Positives (false delay alarms): **5,160**\n","* False Negatives (missed delays): **148,582**\n","* True Positives (correct delays): **10,934**\n","\n","### What this means:\n","\n","* The model correctly caught **10,934 delayed flights**.\n","* It only incorrectly flagged **5,160 on-time flights as delayed**.\n","* Overall accuracy was much higher at **82%**.\n","* Precision for delayed flights was strong (68%), but recall was low (7%) at the default threshold.\n","* After applying the tuned threshold (~0.323), recall improved to ~30% while keeping precision near 48%.\n","\n","In simple terms:\n","\n","> LightGBM is much more conservative. It avoids false alarms and maintains high overall accuracy, but it misses many delayed flights unless the decision threshold is lowered.\n","\n","---\n","\n","# Direct Comparison\n","\n","| Model                      | True Delays Caught | False Delay Alarms | Recall (Delayed) | Precision (Delayed) | Accuracy |\n","| -------------------------- | ------------------ | ------------------ | ---------------- | ------------------- | -------- |\n","| Logistic Regression        | 100,216            | 294,418            | 63%              | 25%                 | 59%      |\n","| LightGBM (Default 0.5)     | 10,934             | 5,160              | 7%               | 68%                 | 82%      |\n","| LightGBM (Tuned Threshold) | ~47,863            | ~52,625            | 30%              | 48%                 | 81%      |\n","\n","---\n","\n","# Key Insights\n","\n","1. Logistic Regression catches more delays but generates an extremely high number of false alarms.\n","2. LightGBM significantly reduces false alarms and improves overall reliability.\n","3. Threshold tuning allows LightGBM to improve recall while maintaining reasonable precision.\n","4. LightGBM provides a better balance between operational usefulness and predictive performance.\n","\n","---\n","\n","# Final Conclusion\n","\n","Both Logistic Regression and LightGBM were evaluated on an unseen test dataset to compare performance. Logistic Regression detected a large portion of delayed flights (63% recall) but generated a very high number of false delay warnings, resulting in low overall accuracy (59%). In contrast, LightGBM maintained strong overall accuracy (82%) and significantly reduced false alarms. While the default LightGBM model was very conservative, applying a tuned probability threshold improved its ability to detect delayed flights while preserving reasonable precision. Overall, LightGBM provides a better balance between reliability and delay detection, making it more suitable for practical operational use and more deployable approach.\n","\n","---\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"SCFYFzSXpfY8"}}],"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[{"file_id":"1F-pXhbaVFZhWW2zK7TMbhFjOP9aOH08A","timestamp":1772499204012},{"file_id":"1zzTElEP1zXmSSSKJA_Bj-A275Y3md4MK","timestamp":1770079410305},{"file_id":"https://storage.googleapis.com/kaggle-colab-exported-notebooks/rapo1973/predicting-flight-delays-using-machine-learning.81d15a08-2a0c-4e27-bb79-a586d61f1821.ipynb?X-Goog-Algorithm=GOOG4-RSA-SHA256&X-Goog-Credential=gcp-kaggle-com%40kaggle-161607.iam.gserviceaccount.com/20260202/auto/storage/goog4_request&X-Goog-Date=20260202T171222Z&X-Goog-Expires=259200&X-Goog-SignedHeaders=host&X-Goog-","timestamp":1770052390132}]},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"datasetId":810,"sourceId":1496,"sourceType":"datasetVersion"}],"dockerImageVersionId":30918,"isGpuEnabled":fal